review_blob: Pours a copper colour, with a good head that diminishes but skeeps standig there. Great compact lace. Aroma of caramel, honey, cocoa, red fruits.Promising. Light body, creamy and thick palate. Taste of cocoa, honey, caramel, red fruits. Hey, this ones really good. Only a little bit more presence in the body is needed.

Deep golden colour, big head that fades leaving a ring but not lace. Aroma of tropical fruits, resine, pine.Medium body, fizzy carbonation. Taste of tropical fruits, pine is present too, some citrus, peaches. Sweeter than expected, though the bitterness is there too.
beer_name: Mikkeller Amass B&W; West Coast Style India Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours a copper colour, with a small head that fades soon, but leaves a good lace. Aroma of caramel, toffee, butter, red fruits. Medium to light body, thick palate. God carbonation. Taste is similar to the smell, adding notes of citrus. Good.

Amber-orange colour, with a one finger head that fades soon, leaving a small lace. Aroma of tropical fruits, malts, caramel. Medium to full body, lively carbonation, creamy palate. Taste of tropical fruits, grapefruit, caramel. Good one, though I expected it not so sweet.
beer_name: Les Trois Mousquetaires S.S. Pale ale amricaine

review_blob: Pours a golden colour, qieth a tow finger head that does not last quuite long, but leaves a good lace and ring. Aroma of papaya (intense), some citrus notes. Medium body, lively carbonation. Taste of papaya, citrus, peaches. Theres a bit of unexpected sweetness too. Good.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Pours a deep amber colour, with reddish reflection to the light. Two fingers creamy head that holds all the while, and a creamy lace all around the glass. Aroma of banana, chocolate, cloves, rainsins, rum. Medium body, palate is dense and thick. Taste of chocolate, bananas, clove, vanilla, rum. If anybody told me its aged in oak, Id believe it. Great.

Nice amber colour, small headthat leaves a ring, and a good lace with teardrops. Aroma of caramel, dark fruits, nuts, butter. Medium body, thick rough palate. Taste of caramel, dark fruits, nuts. Astringent finish. Good one.
Gloden colour, two fingers head that sticks all the while. Aroma of grains, Saaz hops. Medium to light body. Simple taste of grains, citrus. Medium carbonation. Finish ys dry and bitter. Correct.

Clear golden colour, with a small head that fades soon, almost no lace. Aroma of wood, some citrus, peach, tobacco. Medium body, flat carbonation. Taste is sweet, f peach, citrus, tobacco. I cant find the IPA character. Mild beer.

Amber reddish colour, with a normal head that does not last. No lace. Smell of damp earth, grains, toasted malts and nots of caramel. Medium to light body, a little bit watery but crispy palate. Taste of toasted malts, grains, notes of caramel. Aftertaste is bitter, but noticing the caramel. Not bad.

Almost black colour, small head that fades soon leaving a small lace. Fainated smell of coffee, chocolate. Medium to light body, flat carbonation. Taste of chocolate, toffee and some hints of licorice.
UPDATED: APR 23, 2016

Golden colour with a two fingers head that tades soon, leaving some ring on the sides and a good lace. Smell of fruits, hops, pine, tropical fruits. Medium to light body and average carbonation. Fainted taste of citrus, tropical fruits and effervescent C vitamin.

Pours an amber colour, with a small white head that fades soon, leaving a ring and lace. Smell of chocolate, spices, cherries, nuts. Medium body and average carbonation. Taste of chocolate, cherries, hints of nuts.

Deep golden colour, tow fingers head that fades soon, leaving a good lace.
Aroma of herbs, citrus, fruits, notes of caramel. Medium body and average carbonation. Tasteof citrus, fruits, perpery, notes caramel. Dry finish.
Hazy golden colour, with a big head that fades leaving a great lace. Aroma is hoppy, herbs, pine, resine. MEdium to full body, flat palate. Taste of grains, bread, hops.
Hazy golden colour, small head that leaves a dense lace. Aroma of tropical fruits, pine,. Madium to full body, crispy palate.Taste of tropical fruits, hops, notes of toffee, fruits.
beer_name: BrewDog Restorative Beverage For Invalids and Convalescents

review_blob: Hazy golden colour, pours a small head that leaves a great lace. Smell of tropical fruits, pine, notes of honey. Medium body, bittersweet, crispy and salty palate. Aroma is hoppy, tropical fruits, notes of caramel. Bitter finish.
beer_name: Brewfist Czech Norris Walker Imperial Pils

review_blob: Hazy golden colour, small head that fades soon keaving a good lace. Aroma of grains, malt, some sweet notes. Average carbonation. Taste is sweet, milk chocolate, fennel.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Hazy golden colour, with a big head that does not hold for too long, leaving a good lace. Aroma of cloves, banana, bepaches, melon. Madium body, lively carbonation. Taste is the same as the aroma, with some lemon notes and some sweetness in the end.

Hazy golden colour, small head that fades soon, leaving some lace. Smell of barn, coriander, oranges, notes of honey. Full body, astringent palate, excessive carbonation. Taste of honey, oranges, spices, coriander.

Deep amber colour, with an enormous head that lasts forever. Aroma is tropical fruits, honey, spices, citrys, caramel. Full body, fizzy carbonation, thick palate. Taste of tropical fruits, honey, orange, herbs. Really good.

Amber colour, two fingers head tha fades leaving a ring and a great lace. Smell is hoppy, coriander, notes of oranges, spicy, fruits. Almost full body, lively carbonation. Taste is like the smell: Coriander, oranges, spicy, resines. Very good.

Dark brown colour, with a two fingers off white head that fades leaving a ring and a great lace. Smell of dark fruits, raisins, prunes, spices. Medium to full body,, good carbonartion, thick palate. Taste of prunes, figs, raisins, spices, cinnamon, chocolate. Supposedly, they use the original Westvleteren yeast.and they have the recipe, since Westvletern was made at this abbey long ago. Just as good or almost as Westvleteren, and cheaper.

Red brown colour, with small head that fades soon, good lace. Smell of pepper, cloves, cinnamon, aniseed, dark fruits. Medium to full body, with a rich, creamy and thick body. Taste is similar to the smell, chocolate, dark fruits, cinnamon, cloves, aniseed. Simply great.

Dark brown colour, creamy big off white head that lingers all the while. Great lace. Smell of candied sugar, caramel, milk chocolate, hints of xerry wine and red fruits. Medium to full body, lively carbonation. Taste of caramel, cherries, chocolate. Finish with some toasted nuances.

Deep golden colour, two fingers head that fades soon. Great lace. Smell is malty, yeast, dried fruits, slithly citrus, peach. Medium to full body, fizzy carbonation. Palate is thick and astringent. Taste is spicy, candied sugar, fruits. alcohol is very noticeable, as it warms your throat and stomach. Dry and astrigent finish.

Poured in my Kasteel glass. Deep brown colour, small beige head with a rich lace. Aroma of dark and dried fruits, plums, cherries, brown sugar, "oloroso" xerry, wood. Medium to full body, creamy and thin palate, good carbonation. Taste of plums, cherries, dried fruits, chocolate, xerry, oak. alcohol is noticeable. Just like an aged Kasteel bruin: Extraordinary.

Cloudy orange colour, two fingers head that fades soon. Almost no lace. Aroma of tropical fruits, oranges, pine, notes of roasted malts. Medium body, full carbonation, thick palate. Taste of tropical fruits, tangerines, herbs. Astringet finish. Good.

Hazy deep golden colour, whit a two finger head that sticks to the glass and leaves a ring on the surface. Smell is fruity, oranges, melon, caramel. Theres something I dont like, maybe some metallic notes. Medium body, great carnation. Taste of oranges, cinnamon, fruity, Both pata and taste have the same disgusting touch of aroma.

When I puiled out the cork, I saw some dirty just behind, so I guess this is not in good conditions.Deep golden colour, big head that lasts forever,great discontinous lace. Smell of oranges, apples, coriander, some clove. Medium body, lively carbonation. Taste of oranges, apples, cinnamon. I need another try.

Dark brown colour, medium head thas does not hold for too long, leaving a tiny lace. Smell of aniseed, clove and some caramel, in a confusing mix. Medium body, good carbonation. Taste of dark fruits, clove, aniseed, everything confusing too. Not the best Chrismast beer at all. Bitter finish.

Deep hazy brown colour with a small off white head that holds for a while, leaving reing and lace. Smell of toffee, pepper, dark fruits, rather a mess when its hard to detect much. Medium body, good carbonation. Taste is peppery, caramel, chocolate, dark fruits. I expected a little bit more, but Ill give another try whenever I can find it.

Hazy gloden colour, with medium head that leaves a ring and a good lace. Smell of banana, cloves, tropical fruits, herbs. Medium compact body, with good carbonation. Taste is hoppy, fruits, flowers, pepper. Anotherone very good Carolus.

Brown colour, creamy, off white head that fades to a ring and lace. SMell of dark fruits, candied fruits, spices(cinnamon, cloves, cardamom).Medium body, grat carbonation, sweet palate. Taste of "polvorones", candied fruits, anise, cinnamon, cardamom, ginger, nutmeg... Very complex. And great.

Pours an off white creamy head, that lingers on. Great lace. Almost black colour, with some red hints when held to the light. Smell of licorice, dried fruits, prunes or figs, chocolate. A bit thin body and not much carbonation. Taste of chocolate, licorice, dried fruits.

Hazy golden colour, small head that fades soon, leaving a good lace. Sour aroma of grass, fruits (pomelo?), coriander, cinnamon, pepper. Medium to light body, soft carbonation. Taste is sweet, fruity, hot, pepper, roses. Spicy and bitter finish. Great.

Deep brown colour, reddish tones to the light. Off white big head, great lace.Smell of chocolate, toasted, coffee, prunes, dried fruits. Medium to full body, compact creamy palate. Taste of dried fruits, chocolate, caramel. Complex.And great.

Amber colour, big head that fades soon leaving some lace. Smell of limestone, dark fruits and a disgusting tyres strong notes. Medium body, good carbonation. Taste of caramel, dark fruits. No hint of tyres here.

Tasted in a Kwak Glass. Clear amber colour, big head that holds on. Smell is spicy, ginger, pepper, caramel. Clean silky palate, medium body. Taste is spicy too: ginger, black pepper, notes of caramel. Sweet finish. Really good stuff.

Black colour, off white head that last forever, great lace. Smell of dark fruits, chocolate, coffee, roasted malts. Medium body ( I miss some more here), good carbonation. Taste of chocolate, dark fruits, coffee, licorice, caramel.

Amber colour, small head that fades soon, good lace. Smell of sulphur, caramel. Medium body, good carbonation. Rough palate. Taste of caramel, apples, some fruit. Not really the best Anchor I know, guess Ill have to give it another try.

Amber colour, big creamy head that holds all the while, great lace. Smell of hops, pine, tropical fruits (though less than usual in IPAs), caramel. Crispy palate, medium to full body and great carbonation. Taste of hops, citrus, pine,some caramel Bitter finish.

Botlle with the label "Open rocknroll". Deep golden colour, big head that diminishes but does not fade. Enormous lace. Smell of herbs, tropical fruits, spices, pepper, Medium body, full, or almost, carbonation. Creamy palate, taste of spices, pepper, fruits, orange. Bitter and spicy (hot) finish. Really good.

Pale blonde colour, almost like a white beer , with a small head that keeps a ring and leaves a great lace. Aroma of pineapple,banana, coriander. Medium to light body, great carbonation. Taste of fruits, bitersweet, cloves. Good.

Hazy golden our, with a big head that sticks forever and leaves an norms lace. Smell of bananas, clove, apricot. I feel some tobaco notes. Great carbonation, body is medium-light. Taste of bananas, clove, citrus, apricot. Good.
Pale golden colour, with a head that doesnt hold. Smell of yeast, maybe flowers. Thin body, taste is bready, some maltiness. Nothing more. Good label, either.

Hazy golden colour, big creamy head that lasts for a good while, leaving a ring and lace. SMell of tropical fruits, citurs, pine, fruits, spices. Medium to full body, great carbonation. Taste of tropical fruits, bananas, clove, spices, citrus. Great.

Orange colour, with a head that fades leaveng a ring and some lace. Smell of tropical fruits, pepper, pine. Medium body, great carbonation. Taste of resin, tropical fruits, caramel, pepper, theres some sweetness there too. Good.
beer_name: Rogue Nation Brutal India Pale Ale

review_blob: Copper colour, big head wiht decen retention, good lace. Sharp smell of herbs, with some caramel and banana. Medium body, good carbonation. Taste of fruits (banana), caramel, herbs. Really good.
